==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Semivowel
<hw>Sem"i*vow`el</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Phon.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>A sound intermediate between a vowel and a consonant,
or partaking of the nature of both, as in the English <xex>w</xex> and
<xex>y</xex>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The sign or letter representing
such a sound.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Semiweekly</ent>⟦br⟧
